show-metadata="false"
expanded="true"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>2472</fr:anchor><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>1</fr:month><fr:day>30</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
href="jonmsterling.xml"
type="local"
addr="jonmsterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:parent>jms-00N3</fr:parent></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
 <fr:p>The <fr:link
href="jms-00KI.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00KI">identity function</fr:link> is clearly <fr:link
href="jms-00KI.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00KI">injective</fr:link>, as <fr:tex>a_0=a_1</fr:tex> implies <fr:tex>a_0=a_1</fr:tex>.</fr:p>

 <fr:p>Let <fr:tex>f \colon  A \rightarrowtail  B</fr:tex> and <fr:tex>g \colon  B \rightarrowtail  C</fr:tex> be <fr:link
href="jms-00M0.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00M0">injections</fr:link>. To show that the <fr:link
href="jms-00KI.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00KI">composite function</fr:link> <fr:tex>g \circ  f \colon  A \to  C</fr:tex> is <fr:link
href="jms-00MO.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00MO">injective</fr:link>, we fix <fr:tex>a_0,a_1 \in  A</fr:tex> to check that <fr:tex>g { \mathopen {} \left ( f { \mathopen {} \left ( a_0 \right ) \mathclose {}} \right ) \mathclose {}}  = g { \mathopen {} \left ( f { \mathopen {} \left ( a_1 \right ) \mathclose {}} \right ) \mathclose {}}</fr:tex> implies <fr:tex>a_0=a_1</fr:tex>. Because <fr:tex>g</fr:tex> is <fr:link
href="jms-00MO.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00MO">injective</fr:link>, we have <fr:tex>f { \mathopen {} \left ( a_0 \right ) \mathclose {}} =f { \mathopen {} \left ( a_1 \right ) \mathclose {}}</fr:tex>; therefore, because <fr:tex>f</fr:tex> is <fr:link
href="jms-00MO.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00MO">injective</fr:link>, we have <fr:tex>a_0=a_1</fr:tex> as desired.</fr:p>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree><fr:p>Now that we have enough definitions in hand to see it, the import of <fr:ref
addr="jms-00M7"
href="jms-00M7.xml"
taxon="Theorem"></fr:ref> is then to state that a <fr:link
href="jms-00KF.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00KF">function</fr:link> is <fr:link
href="jms-00KR.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00KR">bijective</fr:link> if and only if it is both <fr:link
href="jms-00MO.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00MO">injective</fr:link> and <fr:link
href="jms-00M8.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-00M8">surjective</fr:link>.</fr:p><fr:tree
xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"
toc="true"
